<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-675] multiple backslashes and backslash plus dollarsign are not correctly interpreted</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-675</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the folowing lines are failing&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  assert &quot;\\$&quot;==&quot;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&quot;+&quot;$&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
  assert &quot;\\\\&quot;==&quot;\\&quot;+&quot;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but the following are not&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  assert &quot;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;$&quot;==&quot;$&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
  assert &quot;\\\\&quot;==&quot;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
  assert &quot;\\\\\\&quot;==&quot;\\&quot;+&quot;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
  assert &quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;==&quot;\\&quot;+&quot;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
  assert &quot;\\\\\\\\\\&quot;==&quot;\\&quot;&lt;ins&gt;&quot;\\&quot;&lt;/ins&gt;&quot;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
  assert &quot;\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;==&quot;\\&quot;&lt;ins&gt;&quot;\\&quot;&lt;/ins&gt;&quot;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2 backslashes are reduced to just one backslash, and the dollar sign seems to &quot;consume&quot; the leading backslash&lt;/p&gt;</description>
